# Browser Automation Keyword (clouds-f)

Canonical source: `SKILL.md` in this skill root.

Apply this rule when the user asks to open websites, fill forms, click UI elements, capture screenshots, scrape page data, or automate browser workflows.

## Required Execution Loop

1. `agent-browser open <url>`
2. `agent-browser snapshot -i`
3. Interact with refs from snapshot
4. Wait for async updates
5. Re-snapshot after navigation or DOM mutations

## Selector Priority

1. Snapshot refs (`@e*`)
2. Semantic locators (`find role`, `find label`, `find placeholder`, `find testid`)
3. CSS/Text/XPath fallback only when required

## Reliability Rules

- Always use explicit waits for async flows (`wait --load networkidle`, `wait --url`, `wait --text`).
- Re-snapshot after every meaningful page change.
- Use `screenshot --annotate` for visual reference mapping.
- Use `frame @eX` and `frame main` for iframe-scoped tasks.

